eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - It’s becoming increasingly difficult for people in KwaZulu-Natal to get fuel. Long queues are forming all over the province as motorists try to fill up. READ: Violence in SA | Unrest prompts fears of food and fuel shortages Meanwhile, the Department of Energy has announced that the sale and dispensing of petrol and diesel into portable containers is prohibited. The decision comes amid the unrest in KwaZulu-Natal and Gauteng. Countless buildings have suffered extensive damage as a result of arson.